# Cloudflare deploy · MCP only

## Worker identity

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Worker name | `brmste-com-coming-soon` |
| Account ID | `7ea6547b1d6eb1cbd6d0ac5cf960ce2a` |
| Health page token | `brmste-coming-soon-v5` |
| Site assets | `coming-soon/site/` |
| Handler | `coming-soon/src/index.js` |

## Agent deploy flow (Cursor)

1. **Inventory** — `Cloudflare-bindings` → `workers_list` / `workers_get_worker` with `scriptName: brmste-com-coming-soon`.
2. **Deploy** — `Cloudflare-builds` (must be connected in Cursor). Use builds/deploy tools; do not ask for `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN`.
3. **Verify** — `curl https://<domain>/health` or `Cloudflare-observability` logs. Expect `"page":"brmste-coming-soon-v5"`.
4. **Routes** — zone route attachment may require Builds MCP or CI; never prompt user to paste route tokens.

## Local preview (no tokens)

```bash
cd coming-soon && npm ci && npx wrangler dev
```

Wrangler local dev does not require MCP; production changes use MCP or GitHub Actions secrets (operator-managed, not chat).

